Definition: an outward or token appearance or form that is deliberately misleading
Example: he hoped his claims would have a semblance of authenticity; he tried to give his falsehood the gloss of moral sanction; the situation soon took on a different color
Synonyms: gloss, verb, communication, color, colour, appearance, an, outward, or, token, form, that, is, deliberately, misleading, he, hoped, his, claims, would, have, a, of, authenticity, tried, to, give, falsehood, the, moral, sanction, situation, soon, took, on, different
Category: noun.attribute
